{"type":"message","id":"8ffc6e5d","parentId":"ecac482d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:24:39.766Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7r97iuf93qzc_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4483\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2353\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[master ed7d7ca] pulse: 2026-03-24 152414\n 5 files changed, 313 insertions(+), 103 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 152414.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 152414.mutation\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 152414 - The CFI compression experiment identified that binary thresholds (CFI � 0.7 AND freq < 60) fail because \"constant format\" tokens like \"pulse\" (freq=160, CFI=1) look causal but aren't. The next step is to implement and test the hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120).\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"plaid-shore","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4483\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2353\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[master ed7d7ca] pulse: 2026-03-24 152414\n 5 files changed, 313 insertions(+), 103 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 152414.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 152414.mutation\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 152414 - The CFI compression experiment identified that binary thresholds (CFI � 0.7 AND freq < 60) fail because \"constant format\" tokens like \"pulse\" (freq=160, CFI=1) look causal but aren't. The next step is to implement and test the hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120).\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380279765}}
{"type":"message","id":"eb771c75","parentId":"8ffc6e5d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:24:39.768Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7r97iuf93qzc_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 152315\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and insights:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. A key finding from the session: CFI compression experiment shows CFI gives +32.9% precision but loses 92.9% recall\r\n3. The \"Constant Format Problem\" is identified - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n4. A new insight: need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n5. Next experiment is defined: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring\r\n\r\nThe pending action clearly states:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe key files mentioned:\r\n- `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` - the previous experiment doc\r\n- pulse.ps1 - the pulse script\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to:\r\n1. Create the experiment script/plan for the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment\r\n2. Or update the synthesis document with the experiment design\r\n\r\nGiven that the last pulse noted \"No mutations applied this cycle\", I should make a concrete mutation. The most logical next step is to design the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment and document it, which then needs to be run.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: Design and document the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment, so it can be executed in the next pulse.\r\n\r\nI'll update the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md with the next experiment design, or create a new experiment plan.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll focus on creating a structured experiment document that captures the scoring methodology and testing approach. The goal is to precisely define how the hybrid scoring will work and validate its effectiveness in distinguishing between constant and research-related tokens.\r\n\r\nThe experiment design will need to:\r\n- Implement the scoring formula\r\n- Set up a clear 80/20 split testing methodology\r\n- Define metrics for comparing against binary thresholds\r\n- Ensure reproducibility of the experimental setup\r\n\r\nThis document will serve as a concrete blueprint for the next phase of the CFI compression research, providing clear guidelines for executing and validating the new scoring approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified a critical finding: constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts that pure CFI thresholding cannot distinguish from true research tokens. The next concrete step is to design and document the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment that tests the proposed formula.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) by updating the synthesis document with the concrete test plan, scoring formula, and expected outcomes so it can be executed in the next pulse.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```markdown\r\nold_text: ## Pending\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFIÃ-Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) Ã- min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freqâ‰ˆ160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n1. **The gap IS the compression** - session boundaries are temporal hashing\r\n2. **Î» encodes both** - decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\r\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** - Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\r\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** - session gaps as compression is novel and correct\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n- Breakaway is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\r\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\r\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\r\nnew_text: ## Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\n### Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- DEPRESS constant-format tokens: score(\"for next instantiation\") = 1.00 × min(1, 160/120) = **1.0** (still high - FAIL case)\r\n- ELEVATE research tokens: score(\"Phase 1\") = 0.96 × min(1, 136/120) = **1.0** (high - OK)\r\n- PENALIZE low-frequency: score(once-only token) = 0.8 × min(1, 1/120) = **0.0067** (near-zero)\r\n\r\n**Problem identified:** freq/120 caps at 1.0, so constant-format tokens (freq=160) still score 1.0.\r\n\r\n### Revised Formula\r\n`score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/100) × (freq(T) >= 3 ? 1 : 0)`\r\n\r\nThis adds:\r\n1. Frequency cap at 100 (reduces 160→100 effect)\r\n2. Minimum frequency gate at 3 (eliminates noise)\r\n\r\n### Experiment Design\r\n1. Dataset: 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split\r\n2. Compute scores for all tokens\r\n3. Compare against:\r\n   - Binary C\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:23:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380279766}}
